# Git Worktree Safe Staging

Use this protocol whenever making changes across one or more repos.

## Required Preflight

- Run `git status --short --branch` before editing.
- If files are already modified and unrelated to the requested change, do not edit them.
- If a target file already has unexpected modifications, stop and ask the user before proceeding.

## Edit Scope Rules

- Prefer creating new files over editing already-dirty files when adding new guidance.
- Re-read each target file immediately before writing if parallel work may be happening.
- Keep ownership boundaries clear when touching multiple repos in one task.

## Commit and Push Safety

- Stage only explicit paths with `git add <file1> <file2>`.
- Never use blanket staging (`git add .`) in multi-repo or mixed-diff situations.
- Commit only the files changed for the requested task.
- Push only after post-commit `git status --short --branch` confirms a clean state for staged scope.

## Conflict Protocol

- If new unexpected edits appear in a file after you started, stop and ask how to proceed.
- Do not revert or overwrite concurrent changes you did not author.
